columns.name: event_data_store_arn
columns.description: The ID of the event data store.

columns.name: creation_time
columns.description: The creation time of the query.

columns.name: delivery_s3_uri
columns.description: The URI for the S3 bucket where CloudTrail delivered query results, if applicable.

columns.name: error_message
columns.description: The error message returned if a query failed.

columns.name: query_status
columns.description: The status of a query. Values for QueryStatus include QUEUED, RUNNING, FINISHED, FAILED, TIMED_OUT, or CANCELLED.

columns.name: bytes_scanned
columns.description: Gets metadata about a query, including the number of events that were matched, the total number of events scanned, the query run time in milliseconds, and the query's creation time.

columns.name: events_matched
columns.description: The number of events that matched a query.

columns.name: events_scanned
columns.description: The number of events that the query scanned in the event data store.

columns.name: execution_time_in_millis
columns.description: The query's run time, in milliseconds.

columns.name: query_string
columns.description: The SQL code of a query.
